The State Employment and Expenditure For Results (SEEFOR) Project in Bayelsa State has constructed 406 roads and empowered 17, 665 residents across the eight Local Government Areas of the State since its inception in June, 2013. According to SEEFOR, it has also funded the procurement of equipment and renovated critical infrastructure to enhance learning through a School Improvement Plan (SIP) through grants to Technical, Vocational Education and Agricultural Training (TVEAT) which led to an increase school attendance rate of the State. Speaking on Wednesday during a media tour of completed and ongoing projects, the SEEFOR Project Coordinator in the State, Mr. Ayens Adogu, explained that through its strategy of engaging youths in the area of public works, road maintenance and sanitation, it has constructed over 70km of roads across the State. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network Also speaking, the National Project Coordinator of SEEFOR, Dr. Greg Onu, commended the Bayelsa State office for exceeding the target of the project in youth employment and public access to socio-economic services.